title: The Lighthouse Keeper's Secret
author: Brindlewick Wobblequill

scene: Start

You arrive at the base of an old lighthouse on a foggy evening.
The door is slightly ajar. A light flickers from somewhere above.
Your boat is tied at the dock behind you.

Choices:
- Push open the door and go inside -> Main Hall
- Search the dock area first -> The Dock
- Leave while you still can -> Safe Escape

---

scene: Main Hall

The entrance hall smells of salt and old wood. A spiral staircase
leads up toward the light. A narrow door on the left is labeled
"STORAGE". Footsteps creak from somewhere above you.

Choices:
- Climb the spiral staircase -> The Lamp Room
- Open the storage door -> Storage Room
- Run back outside -> Start

---

scene: The Dock

A small rowboat is tied next to yours — someone else is here.
A waterproof satchel sits in the bow. The lighthouse looms behind you.

Choices:
- Open the satchel -> The Satchel
- Go back and enter the lighthouse -> Main Hall

---

scene: The Satchel

Inside the satchel you find a logbook, a compass, and a folded map.
The map shows a small island marked with an X, not far offshore.
You pocket the map.

Choices:
- Row out to the island -> The Island
- Head into the lighthouse with what you found -> Main Hall

---

scene: Storage Room

Shelves of old equipment line the walls. In the corner, a trapdoor
leads down into darkness. A lantern hangs on a hook by the door.

Choices:
- Take the lantern and descend through the trapdoor -> The Cellar
- Go back to the main hall -> Main Hall

---

scene: The Cellar

The cellar is cold and damp. Your lantern reveals a locked iron chest
and a tunnel leading toward the sea. The chest has a three-digit lock.

No choices. This should flag the validator.

---

scene: Wrong Combination

The lock doesn't budge. Something shifts in the darkness behind you.
You decide not to press your luck.

Choices:
- Follow the tunnel instead -> Sea Cave
- Retreat back upstairs -> Main Hall

---

scene: Sea Cave

The tunnel opens into a hidden sea cave. Crates stamped with foreign
ports are stacked against the walls. You realize what this place is.
The tide is coming in fast.

Choices:
- Grab one crate and swim for it -> Smuggler's Ending
- Leave everything and run back -> Main Hall

---

scene: The Lamp Room

At the top of the stairs, an old man sits beside the lamp mechanism,
turning a brass key slowly. He looks up without surprise.
"I wondered when someone would come," he says.

Choices:
- Ask him about the rowboat at the dock -> The Confession
- Back away slowly down the stairs -> Main Hall

---

scene: The Confession

The old man tells you everything. The crates, the tunnels, the island.
He seems relieved. He asks you to decide what happens next.

Choices:
- Turn him in to the authorities -> Justice Ending
- Keep his secret and leave -> Silence Ending

---

scene: The Island

The island is deserted except for a weathered cairn of stones.
Beneath it, wrapped in oilcloth, is a journal dating back forty years.
The lighthouse keeper's name is on the first page.

Choices:
- Row back and confront the keeper -> The Lamp Room
- Take the journal and leave quietly -> Silence Ending

---

scene: Safe Escape

You untie your boat and row away from the lighthouse.
The fog closes in behind you. You never find out what was inside.
Some mysteries are better left alone.

THE END

---

scene: Smuggler's Ending

You surface near your boat, crate in tow, and row hard for the mainland.
By morning you have more questions than answers — and one piece of evidence.
Whatever happens next is out of the lighthouse keeper's hands.

THE END

---

scene: Justice Ending

The authorities arrive by dawn. The tunnels, the crates, the island —
all of it comes to light. The old keeper looks almost grateful.
You never learned his name.

THE END

---

scene: Silence Ending

You leave the lighthouse behind and say nothing to anyone.
Years later, you still wonder if you made the right choice.

THE END
